讀</a></div></div></div><div class="main-content"><h4 id="So-you-want-to-live-tiny-Here’s-what-to-consider-when-choosing-a-house-van-or-caravan"><a href="#So-you-want-to-live-tiny-Here’s-what-to-consider-when-choosing-a-house-van-or-caravan" class="headerlink" title="So, you want to live tiny? Here’s what to consider when choosing a house, van or caravan"></a>So, you want to live tiny? Here’s what to consider when choosing a house, van or caravan</h4><p><img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5ac05dad3e2d0940d0038935/1540859959692-Q3YVZJSQ4K4P3ZLHDJTL/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kB6N0s8PWtX2k_eW8krg04V7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z5QPOohDIaIeljMHgDF5CVlOqpeNLcJ80NK65_fV7S1URWK2DJDpV27WG7FD5VZsfFVodF6E_6KI51EW1dNf095hdyjf10zfCEVHp52s13p8g/Model_Price-Sojourner.jpg" alt></p>
<p>I’ve never thought one day that I would see tiny house as an option in my life. Not before I realized how easy and comfy it could be after I had been living in a studio apartment here. It actually took me a while to adopt this small space, since I’ve never experienced of living in the apartment especially a studio one, I got a bit depressed by the narrow space and wondered why people are able to deal with such environment in a urban city. </p>
<p>Now I’ve been living here for almost 5 years and I can tell what benefits of living in a tiny house: </p>
<ol>
<li>Easy to clean. I think this reason is self-explained. It saves more time to do house chores for sure.</li>
<li>Minimise consumption habits. Restricted storage and space help you to re-evaluate your life choices, reduce superfluous stuff. Not only encouraging a minimalist lifestyle but also enhancing a quality one.</li>
<li>A perfect living condition with sustainable and reclaimed material. Such as solar power, rainwater etc.</li>
<li>less noise and light from human made pollution.</li>
</ol>
<p>During this catastrophic bushfire was happening in Australia. I don’t know how many people understand the impact of climate change with alarming consequence. But I do realize the importance of having your own land in this century. Not for business use but a secured land for autarky. As the Podcast-Business Daily that I listened to today, soil erosion and soil degradation will eventually result in lack of food for population. Having land and growing food in a natural way, cutting back on fertilizers and pesticides, giving some time for it to restore. We are now living in a dystopian world, and it’s imaginable that the future for our generation will be even tougher. </p>
<p>Therefore, my plan is to build a tiny house on my own land and living in a self-sufficient lifestyle in the near future.</p>
